criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  individuals must be between 8-12 years old;

          -  subjects must score above 25 on the SCARED questionnaire;

          -  subjects must have access to a smart phone and internet;

          -  individuals must be willing to participate in the research study and providing
             informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  children that present with symptoms of severe depression or suicidality as measured
             with KSADS-PL26;

          -  children that have insufficient knowledge of the Portuguese language;

          -  subjects that are under any current treatment for anxiety disorder or using
             psychotropic medication.
